<para id="RM000000PF5019X" category="C" type-id="300XU" name-id="ES41R-01" from="200601">
<dtccode>P0115</dtccode>
<dtcname>Engine Coolant Temperature Circuit Malfunction</dtcname>
<dtccode>P0117</dtccode>
<dtcname>Engine Coolant Temperature Circuit Low Input</dtcname>
<dtccode>P0118</dtccode>
<dtcname>Engine Coolant Temperature Circuit High Input</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000PF5019X_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00002IR00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>A thermistor is built into the Engine Coolant Temperature (ECT) sensor, of which the resistance value varies according to the ECT.</ptxt>
<ptxt>The structure of the sensor and its connection to the ECM are the same as those of the Intake Air Temperature (IAT) sensor.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>When any of DTCs P0115, P0117 and P0118 are set, the ECM enters fail-safe mode. During fail-safe mode, the ECT is estimated to be 80°C (176°F) by the ECM. Fail-safe mode continues until a pass condition is detected.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<table pgwide="1">
